            "title": "Protagonist Therapeutics Leaps on Report of Possible J&J Deal",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Colin Kellaher </p><br/><p>\n  Shares of Protagonist Therapeutics moved higher after The Wall Street Journal reported that Johnson &amp; Johnson is in talks to buy company, citing people familiar with the matter. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  Protagonist shares were recently up 9.4%, to $73.34. </p><p>\n\n  A deal isn't guaranteed, and the details being discussed couldn't be learned, the people said, the Journal reported. </p><p>\n\n  Protagonist sports a market capitalization topping $4 billion based on Thursday's closing price of $67.04 for the Newark, Calif., clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Colin Kellaher at colin.kellaher@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  10-10-25 1147ET</p></div>",
