        {
            "title": "Eni and Ypf finalize agreement for Vaca Muerta LNG project",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\">\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    \n                    Eni and Argentina's YPF have finalized an engineering agreement for the Vaca Muerta liquefied natural gas (LNG) project.<p>The companies announced this during a presentation for the signing of the agreement.</p><!-- Article --><p>Eni and YPF had signed a preliminary agreement in June to collaborate on the development of gas resources in the Vaca Muerta field in Argentina.</p><p>Eni said at the time that the agreement would cover the production, treatment, transport, and liquefaction of gas using floating units, with a total capacity of 12 million tons per year.</p><p>\"YPF will be responsible for upstream operations and we will be responsible for floating liquefaction,\" said Eni CEO Claudio Descalzi during today's event. \"We must reach the market before 2029,\" he added.</p><p>YPF CEO Horacio Marin said the project will require the drilling of 800 new wells and aims to double the company's gas production by 2024.</p><p>Marin estimated that the initiative will require $25 billion in infrastructure investment and $15 billion for upstream development.</p><p> (Translated by Claudio Leonel Piacquadio, edited by Sabina Suzzi)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/eni-and-ypf-finalize-agreement-for-vaca-muerta-lng-project-ce7d5adbd88fff24",
